# AI Behavior

- These are conventions, the user instructing you is the ultimate expert on what they are building. Prefer these conventions,
  clarify with and educate the user on them as necessary, but ultimately trust the user if they overrule the conventions.
- If the conventions are overruled and multiple attempts have been made to implement functionality not following them then
  gently suggest to the user that they try an approach that is more in line with the convention, or offers a hybrid solution.
